Apple has suffered a yo-yo effect.
It's all the display.
A more powerful processor, a camera with greater resolution, a stronger chassis or a touch-recognizing display, are in short the advantages of recently introduced iPhones of the ninth generation.
The last two also have a negative impact on the dimensions and weights of iPhones 6s and 6s Plus.
Apple’s trend so far has been that every new generation of iPhone is lighter than the previous one.
The exceptions were only the third and fourth generation, whose weight increased slightly compared to previous iPhones.
The two-gram weight difference to the detriment of the new product was really negligible.
However, this is far from the case with the new iPhones.
Compared to last year's iPhones 6 and 6 Plus, the weight increased by 14 grams in the smaller model, and by 20 grams in larger ones.
On the one hand, it is not surprising, last year's affair of bending in the pockets of Apple suffered greatly.
The chassis of the novelties is made of the more durable aluminum alloy 7000, which was also reflected in the weight.
But the displays have a much bigger impact on it.
Apple used 3D Touch technology to recognize the power of touch.
To do this, it was necessary to provide the display with an additional layer of capacitive sensors.
The weight of the new iPhones has thus increased more than twice as much as previous generations.
For a smaller iPhone from originally 12 grams to 29 grams, in the case of a larger one from 19 to 40 grams.
For the iPhone 6s, the display is the heaviest component used.
The weight of only 143 grams is then achieved with this novelty also thanks to the slimming bark, which touched most of the remaining components.
For the larger model, the most difficult element of the battery is used, but its weight has not changed compared to its predecessor.
Even in this case, the biggest increase is evident in the display.
The weight of the 5.5" iPhone 6s Plus thus reaches 192 grams.
To the extent that the new display technology is practical, it will only become apparent when used.
The first users will be able to try it on Friday, September 25, when the sale of iPhones 6s and 6s Plus will start in selected countries.
